The paper deals with algorithms for approximating the size of a minimum vertex cover in a graph, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely categories. The paper also involves complexity analysis and approximation algorithms, which are topics in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as vertex cover is a well-studied problem in game theory.
